HEASY provides scripts to create HTK acoustic models
and use the acoustic model for recognition.
Note the software was written for Linux systems only!

1) Install HTK 3.4.1:
---------------------

- Download HTK source from http://htk.eng.cam.ac.uk/
- Unpack
- Change in build directory
- Run 'make' and 'make install'
- Make sure the location of the HTK binaries is set in the path

2) Install Bash:
---------------

Should be installed by default on most Linux systems.
Tested using bash version 4.2.37(1)-release.

3) Install Perl:
----------------

Tested using perl version v5.14.2.

4) Install htksortdict:
-----------------------

htksortdict will be installed to /usr/local/bin.
Edit the Makefile (located in directory hasr/src/) to change the install path.

- cd src/
- sudo make

